main event: On May 24, 1950, sightings of aerial phenomena were made by military personnel at Holloman Air Force Base in New Mexico.
interesting points: Two objects were observed, with video documentation attempted, but triangulation could not be achieved due to the objects being filmed from different locations., The military report indicates that professional observers, including Lt. Evans, confirmed the sightings., Multiple sightings occurred on different dates, with at least eight objects visible during one event., Photographs were sent to Dr. Menzel at Cambridge, although the case details of those photos remain unaccountable., A possible collision was avoided by a pilot who reported a bright bluish light while flying near Nashville, TN.
location: Holloman Air Force Base, New Mexico, USA
witness description: Military personnel and professional observers including Lt. Evans
